Process to use Stdio 3D for Mongo Connection.

Step-01:
Open "Stdio 3T". Then, Click on "connect" 
> new connection > Manually configure my connection setting > Next > Provide require details:

In "server:" section
Connection name: Test-connection 
Server: Cosmos-DB-Host-URL
Port: 10255

In "Authentication:" section
Select "Authentication mode: Base(SCRAM-SHA-256)"
Username: your-cosmos-db-user-name
Password: your-cosmos-db-password
Authentication DB: admin (It is defauft you need to give it)

In "SSL:" section
"Use SSL Protocal to connect" check it.

After all this configuration click on "test" to check

Once your test is succes then click on connect and save.
